<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;^</b></monoblue></mono><mono><monoblue><b><a href="voidsql.htm">void:sql</a></b></monoblue></mono><mono><monoblue><b>{</b></monoblue></mono><mono><b>insert&nbsp;into&nbsp;access_log
<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(access_date)
<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;values
<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;('</b><monoblue><b>^date_now.sql-string[]</b></monoblue></mono><mono><b>')
<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><monoblue><b>}
<br />
}
<br />
</b></monoblue></mono><normal>
<br />
We get string of format '</normal><mono><b>2001-11-30&nbsp;13:09:56</b></mono><normal>' with current date and time and at once place it into a DB field. Without this method at hand, we would have to put together the needed strings manually. Note: the method doesn't form the apostrophes-you should add them by yourself.
